		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2012"></a><br><code>sle2012/paper18</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2012</a> paper:</span><br><i>On the Reusable Specification of Non-functional Properties in DSLs</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/FranciscoDurán.html">Francisco Durán</a>, <a href="../profile/SteffenZschaler.html">Steffen Zschaler</a>, <a href="../profile/JavierTroya.html">Javier Troya</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_19">10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_19</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1e.html"><span class="tagM">T1E: Reuse</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s main goal is reusable DSL building blocks for specifying/analyzing non-functional properties across DSLs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The setting is the construction and extension of DSLs, including modular language components for NFPs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It provides formal conditions/proofs for conservative extension and supports analyses via model checking.
</li></ul></li></ul>
